GreenBang Guide

Welcome to GreenBang, a lightweight Alpine Linux live ISO with a Wayland desktop.

---

NETWORK

- Wired (Ethernet) connections work automatically.
- Wireless connections can be configured via the network icon in the panel:
  - Left-click the icon
  - Select your network from the list
  - Enter your Wi-Fi password

---

RUNNING COMMANDS AS ROOT (doas)

GreenBang uses 'doas' instead of 'sudo' for running commands with root privileges.

Basic syntax:
  doas <command>

Enter your password when prompted. Your user account must be in the 'wheel' group
(which happens automatically during installation).

Examples:

Install a package:
  doas apk add <package-name>

Update all packages:
  doas apk upgrade

Remove a package:
  doas apk del <package-name>

Edit a system file:
  doas mousepad /etc/hostname

Reboot the system:
  doas reboot

Power off:
  doas poweroff

---

PACKAGE MANAGEMENT

GreenBang uses Alpine's apk package manager. Note: Most package operations require
root privileges, so you'll need to prefix commands with 'doas'. Searching for
packages does not require root privileges.

Search for a package (no root needed):
  apk search <package-name>

Install a package:
  doas apk add <package-name>

Update all packages:
  doas apk upgrade

Remove a package:
  doas apk del <package-name>

List installed packages:
  apk list --installed

Check what's available to upgrade:
  doas apk upgrade --dry-run

